title: Complete coverage: Central Catholic sprints past Nazareth football
text:

Central Catholic's football team made sure its homecoming celebration would be a very happy one Saturday afternoon. 
The Vikings roared out to a 28-point first-quarter lead and never looked back in a 48-27 Eastern Pennsylvania Conference South Division defeat of Nazareth at J. Birney Crum Stadium. 
Central (4-2 overall, 3-2 EPC South) got 234 rushing yards and four touchdowns from senior Alvin Pacheco , and its aggressive defense forced four turnovers from Nazareth (4-2, 3-2).
